.TH "phylink_connect_phy" 9 "phylink_connect_phy" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phylink_connect_phy \- connect a PHY to the phylink instance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" phylink_connect_phy
.BI "(struct phylink *pl "  ","
.BI "struct phy_device *phy "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pl" 12
a pointer to a \fIstruct phylink\fP returned from \fBphylink_create\fP
.IP "phy" 12
a pointer to a \fIstruct phy_device\fP.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Connect \fIphy\fP to the phylink instance specified by \fIpl\fP by calling
\fBphy_attach_direct\fP. Configure the \fIphy\fP according to the MAC driver's
capabilities, start the PHYLIB state machine and enable any interrupts
that the PHY supports.

This updates the phylink's ethtool supported and advertising link mode
masks.

Returns 0 on success or a negative errno.
